title: Sheriff gives Idaho firefighter update after shocking attack
description: Kootenai County Sheriff Bob Norris says that suspect Wess Roley, who ambushed firefighters, later shot himself. Records show that the sheriff’s office and Coeur D’Alene Police had five minor interactions with the 20-year-old. The Sheriff’s office also learned that Roley had ambitions to become a firefighter.

title: Bryan Kohberger agrees to plea deal, avoids trial in 2022 Idaho student murders
description: 30-year-old Bryan Kohberger, accused of fatally stabbing four University of Idaho students in their apartment in 2022, has agreed to a plea deal to avoid trial in his quadruple murder case. #CNN #News

title: Meet the livestreamers covering the ‘Diddy’ trial
description: Over the duration of the Sean “Diddy” Combs trial, influencers have decided to cover the trial by livestreaming from outside the Manhattan courthouse where Combs has appeared. CNN’s Brynn Gingras spoke with some of the influencers who covered the “Diddy” trial.

title: White House: Harvard in 'violent violation' of Civil Rights Act
description: A Trump administration investigation has found Harvard University in “violent violation” of the Civil Rights Act, once more escalating its battle with the school days after President Donald Trump suggested a deal was in sight to end its targeting of the university. #CNN #News

title: Senate 'vote-a-rama' debates Trump megabill changes, inches closer to final vote
description: A marathon voting session on amendments, known as a “vote-a-rama,” is underway in the Senate. Lawmakers are offering changes to President Donald Trump’s “big, beautiful bill” before a final vote. #CNN #News

title: Inside the Starbucks of the future
description: Starbucks is trying to get back to its roots as a local coffee shop as part of its turnaround plan. The company is redesigning stores with comfortable seats and tables, new espresso bars and other elements to try to draw customers back. CNN goes inside a new store in Bridgehampton, New York that's a model for Starbucks' plans.

title: 'On this, Elon's right': Sen. Kelly echoes Musk's criticism of Trump's megabill
description: The Senate continues its "vote-a-rama" on President Trump's "big, beautiful bill." CNN's Brianna Keilar speaks with Sen. Mark Kelly (D-AZ) about Elon Musk's and Sen. Thom Tillis' criticisms of the bill. #CNN #News

title: Dad jumps into ocean after his daughter falls overboard on cruise ship
description: A father jumped into the ocean after his daughter fell overboard from a Disney cruise ship returning to Florida. Both were rescued by the crew aboard the Disney Dream and back to the ship safely.

title: Hottest opening day in Wimbledon’s history
description: As Wimbledon gets under way, temperatures have soared in the UK. The high temperature on opening day surpassed the 2001 tournament for the warmest opening day in the tournament’s 147-year history. #CNN #news #Wimbledon

title: Trump and the unitary executive: Yates and Gonzales on presidential power
description: Fareed Zakaria talks with former Acting Attorney General Sally Yates and former Attorney General Alberto Gonzales about recent Supreme Court rulings, the 14th Amendment and the powers of the presidency. #CNN #News

title: Authorities identify suspect in firefighter ambush
description: Investigators have confirmed the identity of the suspect found dead on Canfield Mountain on Sunday as 20-year-old Wess Roley, according to a law enforcement official. #CNN #News

title: Jury begins deliberations in the Sean ‘Diddy’ Combs trial
description: Jurors are now deliberating in Sean “Diddy” Combs’ federal criminal trial. Combs has pleaded not guilty to federal charges that include racketeering conspiracy and sex trafficking. If convicted on all counts, he could face up to life in prison. CNN's Elizabeth Wagmeister reports. #cnn #news #diddy #diddytrial

title: Latino influencers stick by Trump
description: Tony Delgado and Gabriela Berrospi, entrepreneurs and founders of multimedia brand Latino Wall Street, helped rally the Latino vote for President Donald Trump in 2024. As the administration has escalated ICE raids and deportations this year, they visited Washington D.C. and the White House to advocate for their community and immigration reform. #CNN #News

title: ‘This is not a luxury’: Families in Trump states agonize over GOP’s proposed Medicaid cuts
description: Courtney Leader is a mother of five children, one of whom has cerebral palsy and relies on Medicaid assistance in addition to private insurance to help keep her daughter alive. CNN's Jeff Zeleny speaks to families and organizations in Missouri about the potential cuts to Medicaid, food programs and rural hospitals in President Donald Trump's domestic policy bill.  #CNN #News

title: 'Wildly, categorically inaccurate': CNN fact check of Trump's claims about 'big, beautiful bill'
description: As the Senate "vote-a-rama" on President Trump's "big, beautiful bill" gets underway, CNN senior reporter Daniel Dale fact checks Trump's claims about what the sweeping domestic policy bill contains. #CNN #News

title: UN nuclear watchdog: Iran could again begin enriching uranium in ‘matter of months’
description: The head of the UN’s nuclear watchdog says US strikes on Iran fell short of causing total damage to its nuclear program and that Tehran could restart enriching uranium “in a matter of months,” contradicting President Donald Trump’s claims the US set Tehran’s ambitions back by decades.  #CNN #News

title: Senate kicks off marathon voting session on Trump’s megabill
description: After a weekend of negotiations and delays, the Senate has kicked off its marathon voting session on President Donald Trump’s sweeping domestic policy bill. CNN's Pamela Brown speaks with Rep. Ryan Zinke (R-MT)  about the "big, beautiful bill", Sen. Thom Tillis's objections, and public opinion. #CNN #News

title: Severe heatwave hits Europe
description: Heatwaves have pushed temperatures above 104 degrees Fahrenheit (40 degrees Celsius) in countries across Europe, including Spain, Greece, Portugal and Italy. Firefighters battled a wildfire near Athens late last week, and regions of Portugal were under high alert on Sunday. According to experts, the extreme weather is linked to climate change. #cnn #news #europe #heatwave

title: Jury set to begin deliberations in the Sean ‘Diddy’ Combs trial
description: The Sean "Diddy" Combs trial heads to the jury today, after they receive instructions from Judge Arun Subramanian. The panel heard closing arguments from the defense and prosecution last week. Combs has pleaded not guilty to federal charges that include racketeering conspiracy and sex trafficking. If convicted on all counts, he could face up to life in prison. CNN's Sara Sidner speaks to trial attorney Kelly Hyman about the jury instructions, and CNN's Kara Scannell previews the next developments. #CNN #News

title: Fareed’s take: US strikes on Iran might make the world less safe
description: The only way to ensure Iran does not acquire a nuclear weapon is through diplomacy, Fareed says. While America’s attacks on Iranian nuclear sites were impactful, they won’t keep Iran from a weapon in the long run — and they undermine the rules-based international order.  #CNN #News

title: See swarms of 'lovebugs' invade South Korea
description: Video posted on social media shows thousands of 'lovebugs' blanketing hiking trails on the Gyeyangsan mountain. South Korea is wrestling with an outbreak of the insects, which have been driven into warmer urban areas like Seoul due to climate change, according to a 2022 study.

title: Watch GOP senator's scathing speech about Trump's 'big, beautiful bill'
description: In a fiery speech, Sen. Thom Tillis (R-NC) warned President Trump and Republicans that the Senate version of the sweeping "big, beautiful bill" will break a promise Trump made to not cut Medicaid. Tillis also announced Sunday that he will not seek re-election in 2026.  #CNN #News

title: Tillis gives fiery speech about Trump's 'big, beautiful bill'
description: Sen. Thom Tillis (R-NC) warned President Trump and Republicans that the Senate version of the sweeping "big, beautiful bill" will break a promise Trump made to not cut Medicaid. Tillis also announced Sunday that he will not seek re-election in 2026. #CNN #News

title: 'Terrible': Enten on Trump's 'big, beautiful bill' approval numbers
description: CNN's chief data analyst Harry Enten breaks down new polls on how Americans view President Donald Trump’s “big beautiful bill.”  #CNN #News

title: Police in Idaho say a gunman started a brush fire so he could ambush firefighters
description: A man believed to have fatally shot two firefighters after starting a brush fire on Idaho’s Canfield Mountain was found dead Sunday evening –– ending what authorities describe as a sniper attack on fire personnel and responding police. CNN's Julia Vargas Jones reports. #CNN #News

title: Idaho suspected shooter intentionally set fire, police say
description: Two firefighters were fatally shot while responding to a brush fire in Coeur d’Alene, Idaho. Another man found dead with a firearm on Canfield Mountain is believed to be the only shooter in Sunday’s attacks, according to Kootenai County Sheriff Bob Norris. #cnn #news #idaho #idahoshooting

title: Beyoncé’s 'flying' car prop tilts midair
description: A technical mishap led to Beyoncé’s “flying” car prop to tilt during a Cowboy Carter concert in Houston, with fans capturing the moment on video. The singer was quickly lowered down and without injury, according to Beyoncé’s entertainment and management company.#cnn #beyonce #cowboycarter

title: Multiple shot while responding to brush fire in Idaho
description: Two people, believed to be fire personnel, were fatally shot and others injured while responding to a brush fire in Coeur d’Alene, Idaho, and at least one active shooter continues to fire at law enforcement with high-powered rifles, according to Kootenai County Sheriff Robert Norris.

title: Multiple people shot in Idaho while responding to brush fire
description: At least two people were fatally shot and others injured while responding to a brush fire in Coeur d’Alene, Idaho. At least one active shooter continues to fire at law enforcement with high-powered rifles, according to Kootenai County Sheriff Robert Norris. CNN senior law enforcement analyst chief Charles Ramsey and former Boston Police commissioner Chief Ed Davis join CNN’s Omar Jimenez to discuss. #CNN #News

title: Colombians celebrate Pride in defiance against LGBTQ violence
description: Thousands of Colombians take to the streets of Bogota in celebration of Pride, as well as an act of defiance against violence in the country towards community members.

title: Watch 'Somebody Feed Phil' at the Food & Wine Classic in Aspen
description: From Chicago-style profiteroles to Tyler Florence's truffle-stuffed Wagyu beef, Phil Rosenthal gets everyone to shove delicious food into his mouth in Aspen, Colorado. #cnn #news #travel #aspen #colorado #cooking #wagyu #beef #lifestyle #besttowns #foodie #foodlover #philrosenthal #tylerflorence

title: Thousands defy ban on Budapest Pride
description: Protesters in Budapest are marching against a ban on Pride events across Hungary. People came from 30 different countries to show support under scorching heat, organizers said. #cnn #budapest #hungary #pride #news

title: Why Thailand U-turned its cannabis policy
description: Three years since Thailand became the first country in Asia to decriminalize cannabis, the government this week imposed new rules designed to rein in the country’s “green rush.” #cnn #news #thailand #weed #cannabis

title: Two men reunite baby bird with its mother
description: Two men were walking in their neighborhood when they heard chirping near a sewer. When they approached, they could see a baby bird trapped inside the sewer.

title: Iowa anchor has been missing for 30 years
description:
CNN’s Randi Kaye investigates the mystery of journalist Jodi Huisentruit’s disappearance in 1995. Now thirty years later, police are still tracking down clues.

#CNN #News

title: Newlyweds Bezos and Sanchez spotted on boat ride
description: CNN’s Melissa Bell reports from Venice, Italy, following newlyweds Jeff Bezos and Lauren Sanchez as they wave at spectators during their boat ride through the city. #CNN #News

title: Protesters march in Venice against Bezos-Sanchez wedding
description:
Demonstrators with the “No Space for Bezos” group marched through the streets of Venice on the final day of the extravagant wedding celebrations of Jeff Bezos and Lauren Sanchez. CNN’s Melissa Bell reports from the protest.

#CNN #News #venice #bezoswedding

title: Tens of thousands of protesters at Hostages Square call for an end to the Gaza war
description: CNN's Nic Robertson reports from Tel Aviv where tens of thousands of anti-war protesters packed Hostages Square to call for an end to the Gaza war and the return of the remaining hostages.

title: Don Jr.: 'Affirmative Action' is why Obama won Nobel, not Trump
description: President Trump's desire for a Nobel Prize is no secret and he often blames politics as the reason he hasn't yet won. In an X post, Donald Trump Jr. claimed President Obama won his because of "affirmative action." Abby Phillip and CNN's Table for Five panel debates. #cnn  #News

title: Is Chinese history repeating itself in the US?
description: Scholars and commentators in both the US and China are drawing comparisons between the early months of President Donald Trump’s second term and communist dictator Mao Zedong’s Cultural Revolution. But some believe the way of Mao is unlikely to take root in America. CNN's Kristie Lu Stout explores the similarities and differences between the two leaders. #cnn #news

title: What to expect on the last day of the extravagant Bezos-Sanchez wedding
description: After tying the knot in a private ceremony on Friday, Jeff Bezos and Lauren Sanchez’s three-day-long Venetian extravaganza will come to a close on Saturday with a final star-studded party. #cnn #news

title: Hundreds of women offer babies as martyrs in Tehran ceremony
description:
CNN’s Frederik Pleitgen witnesses the ‘Hosseini Infants Ceremony’ in Tehran where hundreds of women hold their babies into the air to show they are willing to offer their children to God and to Imam Hossein. The ceremony is held on the first Friday of the month in Islamic calendar.

#CNN #News #Iran #Tehran

title: NewsNight 'Off Menu': Bezos-Sanchez Venetian Nuptials
description:
In a CNN NewsNight web exclusive, Abby Phillip and the panel discusses Amazon founder Jeff Bezos' star studded Venetian wedding. #cnn #news #jeffbezos #venice 





 #CNN #News

title: CNN reports from the huge crowds attending state funerals in Tehran
description: CNN's Frederik Pleitgen describes the scene as thousands of Iranians gathered to mourn military leaders, nuclear scientists and civilians during the country’s 12-day conflict with Israel. #CNN #News #Iran

title: Iran mourns victims of conflict with Israel
description: Iran held a state funeral for IRGC commanders, nuclear scientists and civilians killed during the country’s 12-day conflict with Israel. At least 60 people will be buried at the funeral in Tehran, according to state-affiliated media. #CNN #News #Iran

title: Video shows woman clinging to tree as immigration agents try to detain her
description: A bystander captured on video the moment immigration agents in street clothes chased a woman across the street trying to detain her outside of a Home Depot where she had been selling food in West Los Angeles just moments prior.

title: 3-month-old baby's death in Gaza sheds light on humanitarian crisis
description: Despite lifting its 11-week total blockade of Gaza in May, Israel continues to restrict the types of aid allowed into Gaza. CNN's Jeremy Diamond reports on Gaza's most vulnerable.

title: Trump: Canada's new tax is a 'blatant attack' on US
description:
President Donald Trump said he has put an end to trade talks with Canada and will soon announce a new tariff rate for that country, he said in a Truth Social post. The decision to end negotiations, which have been ongoing for several months, came after Canada announced a digital service tax, Trump said, calling it “a direct and blatant attack on our Country.”
 #CNN #News

title: NYC Mayor Eric Adams responds to low poll numbers
description: New York City Mayor Eric Adams joins CNN's Jake Tapper to discuss poll numbers that indicate dissatisfaction with his job performance.

title: Key lines from UVA president’s resignation letter
description: University of Virginia president James Ryan announced his resignation amid pressure from the US Department of Justice to dismantle the university’s diversity, equity and inclusion programs. CNN's Betsy Klein reports.

title: House members briefed on US strikes on Iran nuclear sites
description: House representatives received a classified briefing on Iran today. As CNN spoke to them after the briefing concluded, lawmakers appeared divided along party lines, with Republicans reinforcing their belief that the US strikes were effective and some Democrats expressing skepticism. #CNN #News

title: Lauren Sanchez reveals wedding dress
description: Lauren Sanchez revealed her highly-anticipated wedding dress in an exclusive interview with Vogue where she shared the craftsmanship and inspiration behind her custom Dolce & Gabbana gown.

title: Persian Jews find refuge in 'Tehrangeles'
description:
CNN's Nick Watt reports from Westwood Boulevard in Los Angeles, situated in a neighborhood known as "Tehrangeles" for its population of Iranians and Persian Jews.

#CNN #News

title: What biohacker Bryan Johnson says is the most powerful drug in existence
description: CNN's Boris Sanchez spoke with controversial biohacker Bryan Johnson about the impact of the medical experiments he's done and what he thinks is the most underrated aspect of health.

title: See Jonathan Anderson's highly anticipated Dior debut
description: Jonathan Anderson, founder of JW Anderson, made his debut as creative director of Dior. His collection, Dior menswear Spring/Summer 2026, was showcased during Paris Fashion Week.

description: CNN's Melissa Bell gives a tour of where Jeff Bezos and Lauren Sanchez's wedding ceremony is in Venice, Italy.

description: Bryan Johnson, a world-famous "biohacker," speaks with CNN’s Boris Sanchez about his quest to cheat Mother Nature by trying not to die. #CNN #News

title: Sean ‘Diddy’ Combs’ son escorted out of courtroom
description: A judge removed Sean Diddy Combs’ son, Justin Combs, from the courtroom and apparently asked him to change his clothing after Combs’ son arrived wearing a shirt that says “Free Sean Combs” to the defense team’s final closing arguments. The controversy comes nearly two weeks after Diddy’s son Christian ‘King’ Combs was also removed and spoken to by the judge for wearing a similar slogan in sight of the jury.

title: Celebrities dazzle in their wedding attire as they leave for the Bezos-Sanchez ceremony
description: Corseting, feathers and plenty of diamonds adorn guests as they step into water taxis set to take them to the Friday evening festivities for Jeff Bezos and Lauren Sanchez. #jeffbezos #laurensanchez #wedding #CNN #News

title: Combs attorney says evidence shows a ‘swingers’ lifestyle, and prosecutors exaggerated beyond that
description: Attorney Marc Agnifilo has argued that the prosecution exaggerated its case against Sean “Diddy” Combs and has only shown evidence of his “swingers” lifestyle and personal drug problems, not a criminal enterprise. He also disputed a rape allegation against Combs, which is not among his charges but was raised during testimony. #CNN #News

title: Trump says he'd consider bombing Iran again
description: In a White House briefing with reporters President Donald Trump was asked if he would consider bombing Iran's nuclear sites again if future intelligence reports offered a concerning conclusion on Iranian enrichment of uranium. #cnn #news #trump #iran

title: USNS Harvey Milk new name revealed
description: US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth announced the USNS Harvey Milk is being renamed to the USNS Oscar V. Peterson. During Pride Month in June, he ordered the stripping of the name Harvey Milk who was a gay rights activist and Navy veteran. #cnn #news #politics

title: House lawmakers react to classified briefing on Iran strikes
description: Lawmakers left a classified briefing on Iran today divided along party lines, with Republicans reinforcing their belief that the US strikes were effective, while some Democrats expressed skepticism. CNN's Lauren Fox reports.  #CNN #News

description: "Cobra Kai" star Martin Kove allegedly bit co-star Alicia Hannah-Kim during a fan convention in Washington, claiming it was a joke, according to police. #cnn #news

description: At the White House, President Donald Trump called the court’s ruling a “victory for the Constitution, the separation of powers and the rule of law.”  #CNN #News

description: President Trump thanked conservative Supreme Court justices and explained what he plans to do next after the Court backed his effort to curtail lower court orders that have hampered his agenda for months. #cnn #news #trump #scotus #supremecourt

title: Supreme Court backs parents who want to opt out of LGBTQ+ curriculum

description: 102-year-old Jake Larson, WWII veteran, and his reaction to winning an Emmy for his interview with CNN's Christiane Amanpour.

Follow CNN's Victor Blackwell as he visits Ithaca, New York -- a hidden gem where towering waterfalls, vibrant murals, and soulful food come together to create the ultimate feel-good getaway.

title: Fireball spotted across the sky
description: A ‘daytime fireball’ was caught on video in the sky over South Carolina – causing a sonic boom, according to the American Meteor Society. CNN has reached out to emergency management officials in North Carolina and Tennessee, as well as NASA for comment. #cnn #news

title: See moment suspect lights fire on Seoul subway
description: CCTV footage released by the Seoul Southern District Prosecutors’ Office captures the moment a man lit a fire on a busy subway in the South Korean capital last month. The footage, from May 31, shows passengers running away after the suspect doused the floor of the train carriage with flammable liquid before setting it alight. Reuters reports that according to the prosecutors' office, six people were injured. The prosecutor's office says it charged the 67-year-old man with attempted murder and arson.

title: Exclusive: Details emerge of secret diplomatic efforts to restart Iran talks
description: The Trump administration has discussed possibly helping Iran access as much as $30 billion to build a civilian-energy-producing nuclear program, easing sanctions, and freeing up billions of dollars in restricted Iranian funds – all part of an intensifying attempt to bring Tehran back to the negotiating table, four sources familiar with the matter said.  #CNN #News

title: Brad Pitt's home burglarized
description: The Los Angeles Police Department said a break-in occurred at a house in the Los Feliz neighborhood. A law enforcement source familiar with the investigation confirmed to CNN that it belongs to actor Brad Pitt. #CNN #News

description: A ‘daytime fireball’ was caught on video in the sky over South Carolina – causing a sonic boom, according to the American Meteor Society. CNN has reached out to emergency management officials in North Carolina and Tennessee, as well as NASA for comment.  #CNN #News

description: CNN's Erin Burnett speaks with New York City mayoral candidate Zohran Mamdani about concerns over taxing the city's wealthy to fund his proposed initiatives, and whether it will cause them to leave the city.

title: When is jealousy good for you? | Chasing Life
description:
No, you’re not petty for feeling jealous. Research shows humans experience this emotion even before they can crawl. Dr. Sanjay Gupta sits down with psychologist Dr. Joli Hamilton to demystify jealousy and unpack why the complex emotion is not only natural but could actually be beneficial.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's Chasing Life podcast: https://link.chtbl.com/Q4mrYCYu

title: Girl rescued from sewer in China after seven hours
description: Firefighters rescued an eight-year-old girl trapped in a sewer drain for seven hours in Guizhou, China, according to the local firefighting department. The southwestern province has been hit with heavy rains and floods since June 17, with tens of thousands forced to evacuate, according to Chinese state media. #CNN #News #China

title: Bear on runway forces flight cancellations in Japan
description: A bear running around the runway at Japan’s Yamagata Airport has forced staff to cancel flights on Thursday. Traps set up near the runway have failed to catch the bear but will remain in place, according to airport officials. Flights departing from and arriving at Yamagata Airport on Friday are operating as usual. #CNN #News #Japan

title: Hegseth claims CNN spun Iran reporting. Anderson rolls the tape
description: Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth alleges that several media outlets, including CNN, are misrepresenting the Iran nuclear program in their coverage. #CNN #News

description: President Trump's "Big Beautiful Bill" hit a significant roadblock in the Senate with a Senate rules referee striking down key provisions, saying they don't meet the chamber's strict budget rules. Senators are now scrambling to make changes that would allow the bill to be passed by the July 4th deadline.

title: Zohran Mamdani responds to Eric Adams’ ‘manicured nails’ dig

description: Caine said the strikes against Iran’s nuclear facilities went as planned, and the 30,000 pound bombs dropped “functioned as designed, meaning they exploded.” #CNN #News

title: Source: 'Diddy' won't testify at his own federal trial
description: CNN's Elizabeth Wagmeister explains why Sean 'Diddy' Combs is not expected to testify, according to a source familiar with the federal trial. Combs has pleaded not guilty to charges that include racketeering conspiracy, sex trafficking and transportation to engage in prostitution. If convicted on all counts, he could face up to life in prison.

title: Trump thanks Iran for advance notice on 'weak' missile attack
description: Qatar’s Defense Ministry said its air defenses “successfully” intercepted the missile attack targeting the Al Udeid Air Base in Qatar. No deaths or injuries have been reported. #CNN #News

title: Debris near US base in Qatar
description: Video geolocated and verified by CNN shows burning debris falling next to a highway in Qatar after Iranian missiles fired at US base Al-Udeid were intercepted.

title: Iranian skies light up after attack towards US base in Qatar
description: Following Iran's attack towards a US base in Qatar, CNN's Fred Pleitgen reports from Tehran an increase in anti-aircraft fire in the skies over Iran's capital city. Qatar’s Defense Ministry said its air defenses “successfully” intercepted the missile attack targeting the Al Udeid Air Base in Qatar. No deaths or injuries have been reported. #cnn #news #iran #tehran #qatar

title: Iran fires missiles at US air base in Qatar, no casualties reported
description: Iran has launched a “powerful” attack on a US air base in Qatar, the country’s Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps said. Al Udeid Air Base was attacked “by short-range and medium-range ballistic missiles originating from Iran,” a US defense official said. #CNN #News

title: RSV can cause severe disease for babies. This drug could prevent it
description: RSV is the most common cause of hospitalization in babies, but Sanofi is one of a few companies producing a shot that can help prevent this potentially severe illness. CNN's Meg Tirrell tours one of their facilities. #cnn #health #vaccine #rsv

title: Video shows panic in mall in Qatar
description: Footage shows men, women and children running in panic inside of a mall in Doha, Qatar, after Iran fired missiles at the Al Udeid Air Base.

title: Freak storm leads to tragedy on Lake Tahoe
description: A sudden storm rolled in over Lake Tahoe causing extreme conditions while people were enjoying a sunny summer day.

title: Millions of galaxies revealed in Rubin Observatory's stunning debut
description: The Vera C. Rubin Observatory released its first images, showcasing millions of galaxies. The images are also expected to reveal thousands of previously unknown space objects. #cnn #news #space

title: Dangerous heat wave underway for parts of the US
description: An extremely dangerous heat wave is underway for the eastern half of the United States as a potent heat dome reaches its peak, bringing the hottest temperatures of the year so far – the hottest in years for some cities. CNN meteorologist Derek Van Dam reports. #cnn #news #weather

title: Trump floats Iran ‘regime change’ on social media
description: President Donald Trump suggested the possibility of regime change in Iran in a social media post Sunday. CNN's Alayna Treene reports.

title: Iran targets US-run airbase in Qatar
description: Iran launched multiple missiles toward US bases in Qatar on Monday after the US struck Iran’s nuclear sites over the weekend. Qatar’s air defenses intercepted the missile attack, and there have been no reports of injuries. Still, Qatar condemned Iran’s attack on the Al Udeid Air Base, calling it “a flagrant violation of Qatar’s sovereignty and airspace.” #cnn #news #iran #usa #qatar #doha

title: NATO Secretary General Mark Rutte says US strikes on Iran did not break international law
description: NATO Secretary General Mark Rutte, speaking to reporters during a press conference Monday ahead of a NATO summit in The Hauge, reaffirmed NATO's position that Iran "should not have its hands on a nuclear weapon" and that the US strikes over the weekend on the country's nuclear facilities were not "against international law." #cnn #news #iran #nato #usa

title: Why the Strait of Hormuz is so significant
description: As Iran threatens to disrupt and close the Strait of Hormuz, CNN's Nick Paton Walsh breaks down why this narrow passage is so important.  #cnn #news #hormuzstrait #iran

title: Dashcam captures strike near Ashdod
OKC fans celebrate Thunder’s NBA championship
description: The Oklahoma City Thunder won the NBA championship with a Game 7 win on their home court over the Indiana Pacers. #CNN #News

title: Trump floats Iran ‘regime change’ as Tehran vows to retaliate

CNN’s Brian Todd reports, and Paula Hancocks joins Becky Anderson to discuss.  #CNN #News

title: World leaders divided after US attack on Iran

title: Satellite images show before and after of Iran’s nuclear sites
description: Iran’s largest nuclear complex was dealt a series of severe blows in US strikes on Sunday, a CNN analysis of satellite imagery found. CNN military analyst Col. Cedric Leighton (Ret.) and CNN national security analyst Juliette Kayyem join to discuss. #CNN #News

title: Before and after satellite images show damage to Iran’s nuclear sites
description: Iran’s largest nuclear complex was dealt a series of severe blows in US strikes on Sunday, a CNN analysis of satellite imagery found. See the before and after images, provided by Maxar Technologies, showing the damage visible at three of Iran's nuclear facilities. Initial damage assessments to the three sites are ongoing, according to the UN’s International Atomic Energy Agency. #cnn #news #iran

title: ‘No one dirtier than Trump’: Iranians react to US strikes
description: CNN's Fred Pleitgen is on the streets of Tehran, Iran's capital city, a day after US President Donald Trump confirmed he approved US strikes on Iran. Hear from residents in the city who say the strikes strengthen their support for Iranian leadership. #cnn #cnnnews

title: Exclusive: Iranian FM spokesperson says Trump administration betrayed diplomacy
description: Iranian Foreign Ministry Spokesperson Esmail Baghaei spoke exclusively to CNN’s Fred Pleitgen in Iran after the US attacked three key nuclear facilities in the country. Baghaei said the US’ actions were “unprecedentedly dangerous” and a “betrayal of diplomacy.” #cnn #news #iran #middleeast #trump

title: General describes the moment the US struck #Iran
description: Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff General Dan Caine detailed the moment US B2 bombers dropped Massive Ordnance Penetrator bombs on Iran's Fordow nuclear plant followed by Tomahawk missiles striking Isfahan. The strikes were announced Saturday by President Trump. #cnn #news #iran

title: Iranian foreign minister responds to US strikes
description: The Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi has condemned US strikes on the country’s nuclear facilities. He said Iran continues to defend itself by all means necessary against US and Israeli military aggression, and that the US holds “full responsibility for the consequences of its actions.”

title: Hegseth says ‘American deterrence is back’
description: US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth addressed reporters during a Pentagon briefing Sunday morning following President Trump’s weekend announcement of US strikes on Iran. Trump had said the US had struck Iranian nuclear sites including Fordow, Natanz, and Isfahan. #cnn #cnnnews

title: Here’s what the US used to attack Iran
description: The US launched a significant military operation targeting Iran's nuclear facilities. CNN military analyst Cedric Leighton breaks down which weapons were deployed, including the Massive Ordnance Penetrator (MOP) for the first time in US combat history. #cnn #news #iran #us #trump #israel

title: CNN shows aftermath of first Iranian strike on Israel after US attack
description: CNN International Diplomatic Editor Nic Robertson reports from Tel Aviv where rescue teams are on the scene of an apartment building damaged by an Iranian missile strike. #CNN #News

title: First attack on Israel since US struck Iran
description: Israeli emergency responders deployed to multiple sites after reports of impacts from a fresh wave of Iranian missiles. The strikes were the first by Iran since the US announced it had attacked the country's nuclear facilities. #cnn #news #israel #haifa #telaviv #iran #us #trump

title: Fareed reacts to US strikes in Iran

title: Iran condemns US strikes

title: US strikes Iran: how we got here

President Donald Trump addressed the nation from the White House after US strikes on three nuclear sites in Iran.

#CNN #News

title: This nostalgic symbol could vanish from Hong Kong forever

Toronto native Alan Wu has refurbished one to keep the nostalgia alive for himself and others among the city’s diaspora. #cnn #news #hongkong #travel #taxi #toronto #diaspora

title: Trump announces strikes on nuclear sites in Iran
description: The US “successfully” hit three nuclear sites in Iran, including Fordow, Natanz and Isfahan, President Donald Trump announced. American B-2 bombers were used in the weekend operation, a source told CNN. CNN’s Anderson Cooper reports. #CNN #News

title: Trump announces air strikes on nuclear sites in Iran

title: Mahmoud Khalil met with cheers at airport in New Jersey

CNN’s Gloria Pazmino was at the airport for his arrival, which included the presence of Congresswoman Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez. #cnn #news

title: Hot air balloon accident kills at least 8 in #Brazil
description: A video posted to social media showed a hot air balloon catching fire in the sky before plummeting to the ground in Brazil on Saturday. Eight of the 21 people on board died in the incident, according to the local governor. #cnn #news #brazil #hotairballoon

CNN’s Fred Pleitgen visited a hospital in the Iranian capital of Tehran to hear from residents injured in airstrikes. #cnn #news #iran #tehran #israel

description: A hidden environmental crisis is unfolding in ancient caves near China's Zhangjiajie Forest Park, famed for its massive quartz-sandstone pillar formations, which are said to have inspired the floating scenery that appears in the 2009 Hollywood blockbuster “Avatar.” Viral social media videos showing piles of trash in the area, some reportedly dumped over a decade ago, are prompting a mass cleanup of the karst caves. #CNN #News

title: Here's the latest look at US military assets in the Middle East amid Israel-Iran conflict

title: Video shows missiles from Iran streaking skies of Israel

The military called on the public to "enter a protected space" and stay there until further notice. Israel has also begun a new wave of attacks in Iran, its military said Saturday.

title: Mahmoud Khalil speaks after being released from ICE detention center

The judge found Khalil is not a flight risk or a danger to public safety, saying it’s “highly unusual” to be seeking his detention at this point.

description: As President Donald Trump is warming to the idea of using US military assets to strike Iranian nuclear facilities, officials and experts have suggested the US’ 30,000-pound “bunker buster” bomb is the only weapon capable of destroying the Fordow Fuel Enrichment Plant, a facility thought to be key to Tehran’s nuclear program, which is carved into a mountain and extends deep underground. title: Iran's supreme leader cannot ‘continue to exist,’ Israel’s defense minister says
description: Iran’s Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei cannot be allowed to “continue to exist,” Israel’s Defense Minister Israel Katz said today, after an Israeli hospital was struck by an Iranian missile. Speaking to reporters in the central city of Holon, which was also targeted by Iran overnight, Katz compared Khamenei to the German dictator Adolf Hitler.  #CNN #News

title: CNN goes inside Iranian TV studio destroyed by Israeli airstrike
description: Footage of an Iranian state news bulletin being interrupted by an Israeli airstrike captured attention earlier this week as Israel and Iran strike each other in a dramatic escalation of tension. CNN’s Fred Pleitgen goes inside the TV studio in Tehran, Iran which has been left devastated by the attack.  #CNN #News

title: See inside Iranian TV studio hit by Israeli airstrike
description: Footage of an Iranian state news bulletin being interrupted by an Israeli airstrike captured attention earlier this week as Israel and Iran strike each other in a dramatic escalation of tension. CNN’s Fred Pleitgen goes inside the TV studio in Tehran, Iran which has been left devastated by the attack.

title: Video shows hospital in southern Israel extensively damaged
description: CNN’s Nic Robertson reports from Beer Sheva, Israel, where a hospital has been extensively damaged after Iranian attacks. Iran’s IRNA state news agency has claimed the “principal target” of the missile strike was a nearby technology park it said was used by the Israel Defense Forces (IDF). Retired IDF Colonel Miri Eisin joins CNN’s Becky Anderson to discuss the military targets in the ongoing conflict.  #CNN #News

title: Can Ozempic and body positivity coexist? | The Assignment
description:
Just a few years ago, ‘body positivity’ was everywhere. Then came Ozempic. Audie talks with Virginia Sole Smith, author of "Fat Talk: Parenting in the Age of Diet Culture," about the future of body positivity in an Ozempic world and whether the movement and the revolutionary new class of weight loss drugs can coexist.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's The Assignment podcast: https://link.chtbl.com/M8FSVoFn

#cnn #news #bodypositivity

title: Sole survivor of Air India crash mourns brother
description: Vishwash Kumar Ramesh is the only survivor among 242 on board an Air India flight that crashed in Ahmedabad on June 12. On Wednesday Ramesh attended the funeral for his brother, who died in the tragedy. #CNN #News #India

title: CNN correspondent reports on the ground in Tehran
description: Air defense systems had been activated over Tehran overnight, according to a Telegram post from Iran’s Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps. CNN’s Fred Pleitgen reports on the scene. #cnn #news #tehran #iran #israel

title: Iranian missile strikes commercial area near Tel Aviv
description: CNN's Jeremy Diamond reports from the scene on an Iranian missile strike in the Ramat Gan suburb of Tel Aviv. The incident comes as Israel and Iran trade strikes nearly a week after Israel launched a series of attacks on Iran's nuclear sites and military leadership. #CNN #News #Israel #Iran

title: House bipartisan team cooperates in effort to force Trump to get approval for Iran strike
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins speaks with Representative Ro Khanna (D-CA) to discuss how he is working with a Republican representative in an effort to force Trump to need congressional approval before ordering a strike on Iran. #CNN #News

title: Obama: US 'dangerously close' to autocracy
description: Former President Barack Obama warned that the United States is “dangerously close” to becoming “consistent with autocracies” during a civic group event in Connecticut.

title: Three military options on Iran Trump is likely considering
description: Alex Plitsas joins CNN's Abby Phillip to weigh in on three possible military options that Trump may likely be considering #CNN #News

title: ‘Thrown into chaos’: Iranian filmmaker shares exclusive video
description: CNN’s Erin Burnett shares exclusive video from inside Tehran sent to CNN from Pouria Nouri, an Iranian filmmaker.

title: Trump has reviewed attack plans, awaiting to see if Iran steps back from nuclear program
description: President Donald Trump has reviewed attack plans for Iran but is holding off to see if Tehran steps back from its nuclear program, a person familiar with the matter told CNN. “As President Trump said himself today, all options remain on the table,” a White House official said. #CNN #News

title: Analysis: What is a bunker buster?
description:
There’s only one weapon in the world that can destroy a place like Fordow, and one plane that can carry that weapon. CNN military analyst Col. Cedric Leighton (ret.) explains how the Massive Ordnance Penetrator - a sophisticated bunker buster - works. 

#CNN #News

title: Trump, 'out' of patience with Iran, called Situation Room meeting
description: A Situation Room meeting called by President Donald Trump to discuss US options in the Israel-Iran conflict has ended. A few hours earlier, the US president, who indicated his patience “has already run out” with Tehran, said he has not yet made final decision on whether the US would get involved. #CNN #News

title: Trump says decision on Iran will come down to the last second
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins asks President Trump if he has made a final decision on whether to intervene in the Israel-Iran conflict.

title: Dr. Oz on unveiled plan for cuts to Medicaid, taxes in Trump agenda bill
description: The GOP-led Senate Finance Committee released its proposal for President Donald Trump’s agenda bill that calls for enacting sweeping cuts to Medicaid and preventing a multi-trillion dollar tax hike on Americans. #CNN #News

title: CNN on the ground in #Iran
description: CNN’s Fred Pleitgen is in Iran’s capital city of Tehran and is the first western journalist to enter the country since its conflict with Israel started. Hear his first impressions and what he’s witnessed as he journeyed across Iran. #cnn #news #iran #tehran #israel

title: Crowd cheers for Karen Read as she’s acquitted of murder
description: Karen Read, the Massachusetts woman accused of drunkenly striking her off-duty police officer boyfriend and leaving him to die in January 2022, was found guilty of drunk driving though she was acquitted of the most serious charge of second-degree murder. CNN's Jean Casarez reports from outside the courthouse where Read's supporters reacted to the verdict.

title: Some US embassy personnel and family members evacuated from Israel
description: The United States on Wednesday evacuated some embassy personnel and family members from Israel on a US military aircraft, three sources told CNN. A full evacuation of the embassy has not been ordered and diplomats and family members are not required to leave. #CNN #News

title: Israel’s new normal: sirens and shelters
description: Sirens and shelters are quickly becoming the new normal in Israel's Tel Aviv as the country's military continues to trade missiles with Iran. CNN's Clarissa Ward takes you inside one of the underground shelters as beachgoers in the city heed a pre-alert on their phones and hunker down. #cnn #news #israel #telaviv #iran #siren #shelter

title: Karen Read acquitted of killing her police officer boyfriend
description: Karen Read, the Massachusetts woman accused of drunkenly striking her off-duty police officer boyfriend and leaving him to die in January 2022, was acquitted of the most serious charge of second-degree murder. She was found guilty on a charge of drunk driving. #CNN #News

title: Karen Read acquitted of killing her police officer boyfriend
description: Karen Read, the Massachusetts woman accused of drunkenly striking her off-duty police officer boyfriend and leaving him to die in January 2022, was acquitted of the most serious charge of second-degree murder. She was found guilty on a lesser charge of drunk driving. Read was sentenced to one-year probation and will not serve any jail time.

title: Nezza performs National Anthem in Spanish to protest ICE raids
description: Singer Nezza performed the US National Anthem in Spanish at a recent Dodgers game as a protest against recent immigration raids in Los Angeles. She says a team employee told her not to, but the singer performed the song in Spanish anyway. #cnn #news #sports #dodgers

title: SCOTUS issues blockbuster ruling on gender care for trans minors
description: The Supreme Court upheld Tennessee’s ban on gender-affirming care for trans minors in a blockbuster ruling that will bolster efforts by conservative state lawmakers to pass and preserve other divisive laws targeting transgender Americans. The 6-3 decision by a conservative majority is a major blow to the transgender community and its advocates at a critical time.  #CNN #News

title: Putin pounces as world turns its head to Iran-Israel
description: As possibly the only world leader with a direct line to the White House, Israel Knesset and Iranian leadership, President Vladimir Putin is casting himself as a power broker in the Israel-Iran conflict. CNN’s Matthew Chance looks at how the Russian leader is playing into global affairs as the world turns its attention to Iran-Israel conflict. #cnn #news #russia #putin

title: ‘FOMO foreign policy’: Fareed Zakaria on Trump’s approach to Iran
description: US President Donald Trump said his patience with Iran has “already run out,” but he declined to say whether he has made a decision on US military intervention as the Israel-Iran conflict escalates. CNN’s Fareed Zakaria discusses Trump’s evolving foreign policy toward Iran with CNN’s Wolf Blitzer and Pamela Brown.  #CNN #News

title: Amanpour asks Iranian official how they will respond if US strikes nuclear facilities
description: If the US decides to join Israel in attacking Iran, Tehran would have "no choice" but to retaliate, the Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Majid Takht Ravanchi told CNN on Wednesday.  #CNN #News

title: Third US aircraft carrier group set to deploy close to Israel
description: The USS Ford Carrier Strike Group is expected to be deployed to Europe next week, near the Middle East, putting a third aircraft carrier in close proximity to the conflict between Israel and Iran, a US official and two other people familiar with the matter said. Retired Air Force Col. Cedric Leighton examines the strategic move.  #CNN #News

title: Iran says it'll do 'whatever necessary' if U.S. gets involved
description: CNN's Christiane Amanpour speaks exclusively to Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Majid Takht Ravanchi as the Israel-Iran conflict escalates. #CNN #news #Iran

title: SCOTUS issues blockbuster ruling on gender-affirming care for minors
description: The Supreme Court upheld Tennessee’s ban on gender-affirming care for trans minors in a blockbuster ruling that will bolster efforts by conservative state lawmakers to pass and preserve other divisive laws targeting transgender Americans. #CNN #news #SCOTUS #genderaffirmingcare

title: Karen Read’s father speaks to CNN about daughter's trial
description: A jury is deliberating the fate of Karen Read. Prosecutors allege Karen Read drunkenly struck her boyfriend with her Lexus SUV and left him to die in the snow. Read’s defense contends there was no collision. They have cast her as the victim of a cover-up, alluding to a conspiracy by those who they say killed O’Keefe and framed the defendant, while painting the police investigation as biased and flawed. Read has pleaded not guilty to charges of second-degree murder, vehicular manslaughter while intoxicated and leaving the scene of a collision resulting in death. #karenreadtrial

title: Trump on US striking Iran: 'I may do it, I may not do it'
description: President Donald Trump declined to say whether he has made a decision on US military intervention in Iran. The president suggested the conflict could end soon, saying at one point he did not “know how much longer it’s going to go on.” He added, “The next week is going to be very big.” CNN’s Becky Anderson debriefs President Trump’s statements with CNN’s Paula Hancocks and Middle East expert Aniseh Bassiri Tabrizi. #CNN #News

title: Will Trump order US strike on Iran?
description: President Donald Trump declined to say whether he has decided on US military intervention in Iran. The US has been providing defensive support to Israel since the back-and-forth missile attacks began last week. #CNN #News

title: Hear Iranian leader’s response to Trump’s call for surrender
description: In a pre-recorded message, Iran’s supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei has responded to President Trump's call for the country to surrender, warning that America's involvement in Israel's military campaign would "100% be at their loss."  #CNN #News

title: Tucker Carlson confronts Ted Cruz about Iran
description: The GOP is divided on the US' involvement in the Iran-Israel conflict. Former Fox News Anchor, Tucker Carlson and Sen. Ted Cruz (R-TX) got into a heated exchange during an interview about the tensions.

title: Actor sues Tyler Perry for $260 million, alleging sexual assault and harassment
description: An actor who worked on a TV show created by Tyler Perry has filed a lawsuit alleging Perry leveraged his industry power to repeatedly sexually assault and harass him while keeping him quiet. The lawsuit is seeking at least $260 million in damages. Tyler Perry denies the allegations. #cnn #news

title: ‘Wary’ and ‘frustrated’: Haberman weighs in on Trump’s shift toward Iran involvement
description: CNN political analyst Maggie Haberman joins CNN’s Kaitlan Collins to discuss President Donald Trump’s shifting stance on using US military assets to back Israel’s attack on Iran. #CNN #News

title: GOP hawks clash with MAGA isolationists on next steps in Iran
description: President Donald Trump, who has embraced a more isolationist approach than many of his GOP predecessors, is navigating competing forces within his own party as he contemplates whether to order the US military to strike Iranian nuclear sites.  #CNN #News

title: Jordan's military intercepts Iranian missiles
description: While traveling into Israel to cover the conflict with Iran, Anderson Cooper and CNN's Chuck Hadad captured video of Jordan intercepting Iranian missiles in Jordanian airspace. #CNN #News

title: Professor on his ‘fear’ about Trump amid conflict between Iran and Israel
description: Professor of International Relations at the London School of Economics Fawaz Gerges analyzes President Donald Trump’s statements related to the conflict between Iran and Israel, and explains why he doesn’t see a light at the “end of this horrible war tunnel.”  #CNN #News

title: Gauging the risks of US strikes on Iran
description: President Trump is getting closer to considering using U.S. military assets to strike Iranian nuclear facilities, two officials familiar with the ongoing discussions told CNN. Foreign policy analyst Max Boot joined Abby Phillip at the magic wall to assess the risks of that potential decision. #CNN #News

title: Another deadly day for Palestinians seeking aid
description: Over 50 people were killed and more than 200 injured by Israeli forces in the deadliest incident since Israel began allowing aid into Gaza following an extended siege, according to Palestinian health officials. Israel says it is reviewing the incident. #CNN #News #Gaza

title: Zohran Mamdani responds to NYT not endorsing candidate
description: CNN’s Kaitlan Collins talks with New York City mayoral candidate Zohran Mamdani about the New York Times editorial board’s decision not to endorse a candidate in the race.

title: Journalist live-streamed his arrest by ICE during protest.
description: Salvadoran journalist, Mario Guevara live-streamed his arrest by ice agents during a "No Kings protest" near Atlanta, and is still being held on an immigration detainer. Guevara's attorney, Giovanni Díaz, said Guevara has a "permit" to work in the United States, but he does not have Green Card. In a press conference, Díaz declined to specify under which immigration status or program Guevara is protected.

title: Erupting volcano puts Indonesians on high alert
description: Mount Lewotobi Laki Laki, one of Indonesia’s most active volcanoes, erupted Tuesday, sending an ash cloud high into the air. The country’s volcanology agency has raised the alert level to the highest. #CNN #News #Indonesia #volcanoes

title: This is how the US could get involved in the Israel-Iran conflict
description: CNN's Nick Paton Walsh reports on how the US could get involved in the conflict between Israel and Iran while the countries continue trading strikes for a sixth day, with civilians in flashpoint areas facing waves of attacks.

title: Sources: Trump considering US strikes on Iran nuclear sites
description: Two US officials told CNN that Trump is warming to the idea of using US military assets to strike Iranian nuclear facilities. A senior Israeli official told CNN that Israel is waiting to learn whether Trump will help finish the job of destroying Iran’s nuclear program. #CNN #News

title: Food Network star Anne Burrell dead at 55
description: Anne Burrell, a chef and television personality whose joyful demeanor made her a beloved fixture on the Food Network, has died, according to the network. She was 55.

title: NYC mayoral candidate arrested at immigration court
description: New York City Comptroller and mayoral candidate Brad Lander was released from federal custody Tuesday afternoon, hours after he was arrested by officers at an immigration court in Manhattan when he tried to escort a migrant whom officers were attempting to arrest.

title: 'Life in danger': Israel issues evacuation warning for a district in Tehran
description: The Israeli military told residents in Tehran’s District 18 to evacuate an area that it highlighted in a post on X. It warned that it would carry out strikes against military infrastructure there. “Your presence in this area will put your life in danger,” it said. #CNN #News

title: Woman gives birth to triplets in underground Israeli hospital
description: A woman gave birth to triplets Monday in Israel’s Rambam hospital, one of several in the country that have moved some operations underground as Iranian strikes hit the city of Haifa this week, according to Reuters. #CNN #news #Israel #Iran

title: Trump open to assisting Israel in conflict with Iran
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins gives the latest reporting on the White House debating whether to intervene in the Israel-Iran conflict.

title: Americans cut back sharply on spending last month amid tariffs
description: Americans are feeling a hangover from their tariff-fueled buying frenzy early in the spring. Retail sales fell by 0.9% in May from the prior month, the Commerce Department said, down sharply from April’s downwardly revised 0.1% decline. That was the steepest monthly decline since January and worse than the 0.7% decrease economists projected in a poll by data firm FactSet. #CNN #News

title: Why Kool-Aid and Jell-O are getting a makeover
description: Nearly two months after the US Food and Drug Administration announced plans to work with the food industry to phase out petroleum-based synthetic dyes, one major company says it will begin to comply. #cnn #news #kraft #food

title: Trump’s new phone looks a lot like one from China
description: The Trump Organization says its upcoming T1 smartphone will be “proudly designed and built in the United States.” But experts tell CNN they’re skeptical that goal can be achieved-- and say the T1’s specifications are strikingly similar to a Chinese-made phone already on the market. #CNN #news #trump #trumpmobile #t1 #china

title: CNN analysis explores cause of deadly Dominican nightclub roof collapse
description: Early warnings went unaddressed for years before one of the deadliest building collapses this century at the Jet Set nightclub, a CNN analysis has found. Stefano Pozzebon has the story. #CNN #News

title: 'Unconditional surrender': Trump's warning to Iran as sources say he warms up to US strike
description: US President Donald Trump — who issued a series of warnings to Iran, including calling Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei an “easy target” and demanding “unconditional surrender” — has wrapped a meeting with his national security team, according to the White House. #CNN #News

title: The messages Iranians have sent CNN from Tehran
description: As Israeli strikes zeroed in on Iran's capital city of Tehran, CNN's Clarissa Ward reports from Tel Aviv some of the messages she's received from residents in Iran offering a glimpse into the daily anxieties of living in a country faced with an ever-escalating conflict in the sky. #cnn #news #iran #tehran

title: Watch: First-ever images of sun's south pole
description: Solar Orbiter, a joint mission between NASA and the European Space Agency, is revealing the first-ever views of the sun's south pole. These never-before-seen images offer scientists a chance to better understand our star and its effects on Earth. #cnn #space #sun

title: 'Truly chilling': Lawmaker on Minnesota shooting suspect's list speaks out
description: Officials say the suspect accused of shooting Democratic state lawmakers in Minnesota left behind an apparent hit list with dozens of names in his car after exchanging fire with police outside the home of one victim and fleeing the scene. CNN's John Berman speaks with Rep. Hillary Scholten (D) who was on the list.  #CNN #News

title: Trump calls Iran’s supreme leader 'an easy target’
description: President Donald Trump issued a series of warnings to Iran, calling Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei "an easy target” and saying that America’s “patience is wearing thin.”  #CNN #News

title: See Venetians protest Jeff Bezos’ wedding
description: Locals in Venice have been protesting over the impending nuptials of billionaire Jeff Bezos and journalist Lauren Sanchez, worried that the wedding could lead to overtourism and the mega yachts damaging the local lagoon. CNN’s Barbie Latza Nadeau was in Venice and witnessed one of the protests. #CNN #news #JeffBezos #LaurenSanchez

title: Trump claims ‘we now have complete and total control’ over Iranian skies
description: President Donald Trump wrote on Truth Social that “we now have complete and total control of the skies over Iran.” Trump’s statement comes as Israel and Iran engage in a fifth consecutive day of strikes, with civilians in key conflict zones bearing the impact of the fighting. #CNN #News

title: MyPillow founder loses defamation case
description: A federal jury in Colorado found that one of the nation’s most prominent election conspiracy theorists, MyPillow founder Mike Lindell, defamed a former employee of a leading voting equipment company after the 2020 presidential election.  #CNN #News

title: Trump disputes intel chief Tulsi Gabbard on Iran
description: President Donald Trump disputed his own director of national intelligence, Tulsi Gabbard, on how developed Iran’s nuclear capabilities are and said Iran was on the verge of obtaining a nuclear weapon when Israel struck in recent days.  #CNN #News

title: ‘It’s not good’: Enten on public support for Trump’s ‘big, beautiful bill’
description: Top Senate Republicans are running into some resistance from several key senators about the details of President Donald Trump’s “big, beautiful bill,” potentially complicating plans to deliver that package by their own July 4 deadline. CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten looks at public support for Trump’s sweeping tax and spending cuts bill.  #CNN #News

title: Trump tells CNN reporter why he left G7
description: As President Donald Trump returns to the United States after leaving the G7 summit early, he took questions from journalists aboard Air Force One. Watch his answer to CNN's Chief White House correspondent Kaitlan Collins' question on why he left early.

title: Sources: US intel shows Iran was years away from nuclear weapon
description: When Israel launched its series of strikes against Iran last week, it also issued a number of dire warnings about the country’s nuclear program, suggesting Iran was fast approaching a point of no return in its quest to obtain nuclear weapons and that the strikes were necessary to preempt that outcome. But US intelligence assessments had reached a different conclusion – not only was Iran not actively pursuing a nuclear weapon, it was also up to three years away from being able to produce and deliver one to a target of its choosing, according to four people familiar with the assessment.  #CNN #News

title: 'Why would I call him?': Trump responds to CNN when asked if he's spoken to Minnesota governor
description: President Donald Trump said he will not call Governor Tim Walz after the suspect in Minnesota was charged over the attack on state lawmakers. #cnn #news

title: Trump disputes intel chief Tulsi Gabbard on Iran
description: President Donald Trump disputed his own director of national intelligence, Tulsi Gabbard, on how developed Iran's nuclear capabilities are and said Iran was on the verge of obtaining a nuclear weapon when Israel struck in recent days. #CNN #News

title: Alon Pinkas: ‘Something very interesting’ surrounding Trump’s warning to Iranians
description: Former Israeli Consul General in New York Alon Pinkas joins CNN’s Polo Sandoval on “Early Start” to weigh in on President Donald Trump and the latest developments in the Middle East as new strikes by Israel and Iran fuel fears of all-out war.  #CNN #News

title: Trump says ‘real end’ better than ceasefire in Iran-Israel conflict
description: President Donald Trump told reporters on Air Force One that he’s seeking “a real end” to the conflict with Israel and Iran, arguing it’s better than a ceasefire while also suggesting that giving up entirely on negotiating is a possibility. #CNN #News

title: Daughter of detained immigrant worker speaks out
description: Immigration authorities detained more than 70 workers at a meatpacking plant in Omaha, Nebraska, leaving a community stunned and some families split up, Ed Lavandera reports. #cnn #news #ice #immigration #trump

title: Digg's founder on making social media more human again | Terms of Service
description:
Tech entrepreneur Kevin Rose is relaunching Digg, the Reddit-like platform he founded in 2004. And he’s doing it with an unlikely partner: Reddit co-founder and former rival Alexis Ohanian. They say their goal is to make social media human again. Kevin explains what exactly that means and why now.

Listen to the full episode on CNN's Terms Service podcast: https://link.chtbl.com/3lnBAshL

#cnn #news #tech #socialmedia

title: Trump on internal MAGA criticism: I decide what 'America First' means
description: Facing backlash from Steve Bannon and Tucker Carlson among others for his foreign policy decisions amidst the backdrop of the conflict between Israel and Iran, Trump says he came up with the term "America First" and that he decides what that means. #CNN #News

title: Video shows Pakistani students returning home from Tehran
description: Hundreds of Pakistani students who left their studies in Tehran amid daily strikes on the city by Israel, have crossed back into Pakistan, a local official told CNN. #CNN #News #pakistan #Iran #Israel

title: Trump slams Macron's comment on why he has to leave G7 summit early
description: US President Donald Trump called out French President Emmanuel Macron over his counterpart's suggestion that he left the G7 summit to work on a ceasefire between Israel and Iran. "He has no idea why I am now on my way to Washington, but it certainly has nothing to do with a Cease Fire," Trump wrote on Truth Social. #cnn #news #truthsocial #trump #macron #g7

title: Woman describes helping catch Minnesota suspect
description: CNN's Laura Coates speaks with Wendy Thomas, the woman who flagged down police after she saw the suspect in the shooting of two Minnesota lawmakers.

title: Missing journalist's father responds to reports he was 'executed'
description: CNN’s Erin Burnett talks with Marc Tice, the father of missing journalist Austin Tice, about reports that his son was ‘executed’ in Syria.

title: Salt Lake City shooter caught with rifle at ‘No Kings’ protest
description: Video captured the moment a bystander flagged down police after a shooting occurred at a "No Kings" protest in Salt Lake City on Saturday. Witnesses say the man they flagged police for, later identified as Arturo Gamboa, had a rifle in his bag and pointed it in a crowd moments before. #cnn #news #nokings #trump #saltlakecity

title: Here are the US military assets available for use in the Middle East
description: Retired Brigadier General Steve Anderson shows what military assets Israel, Iran and US have available in the Middle East. #CNN #News

title: Sen. Smith reveals what she told Sen. Lee over post
description:
Dek: Sen. Tina Smith (D-MN) revealed to Kaitlan Collins what she told Sen. Mike Lee (R-UT) over his incendiary social media post.
#CNN #News

title: Inside the race to get goods out of China
description: CNN’s Kristie Lu Stout gets exclusive access on board a US-bound container ship in Hong Kong's port, the frontlines of China's “export rush” chaos as the clock ticks down on a 90-day pause on US tariffs imposed on Chinese goods.

title: Kaitlan Collins explains why Trump left G7 summit early
description: President Donald Trump is heading back early to Washington from the G7 summit in Canada, as the conflict between Israel and Iran enters its fifth day. CNN's Kaitlan Collins reports on the escalating attacks between the two sides and Trump's warning to civilians in Tehran.

title: Minnesota congresswoman reflects on the loss of her colleague
description: Congresswoman Betty McCollum (D-MN) discusses her friendship with State Rep. Melissa Hortman, who was shot and killed in what Gov. Tim Walz says is a “politically motivated assassination." #CNN #News

title: Father of missing journalist Austin Tice speaks out amid reports of his son's execution
description: After a top former Syrian general says that missing journalist Austin Tice was executed by the Syrian regime, Tice’s father Marc Tice speaks with CNN’s Erin Burnett about this latest claim. #CNN #News

title: Trump’s sons announce mobile phone company
description: Trump Mobile, a wireless service created by the Trump Organization, aims to rival US carrier companies like AT&T, Verizon and T-Mobile. The Trump Organization, run by President Donald Trump’s eldest sons Eric and Donald Jr., announced the business and launched a new gold smartphone for pre-order.

title: Trump to leave G7 summit early as tensions persist between Israel and Iran
description: President Donald Trump will depart the Group of 7 summit being held in the Canadian Rockies a day early “because of what’s going on in the Middle East,” the White House said. #CNN #News

title: Trump: 'Everyone should immediately evacuate Tehran!'
description: President Donald Trump warned Iranians to evacuate their capital city in a social media post. “Everyone should immediately evacuate Tehran!” the president wrote on Truth Social, without saying why. #CNN #News

title: Israel: at least 24 killed, 590 injured by Iranian strikes
description: At least 24 people have been killed and nearly 600 injured since the fighting started. CNN's Jeremy Diamond reports from in Tel Aviv. #CNN #News

title: Oil prices drop as Trump says Iran wants to de-escalate
description: CNN's Vanessa Yurkevich breaks down when and how consumers can start to feel the effects of the Israel Iran conflict. #CNN #News

title: The NHL's Stanley Cup's perfect imperfections
description: The Stanley Cup is one of the most iconic trophies in all of sports, but one of the reasons the NHL’s championship trophy is so lionized is its perfect imperfections. CNN’s Coy Wire spoke to The Keeper of the Cup Howie Borrow for a tour of some of the trophy’s character-building bloopers.

title: Minnesota 'political assassination' suspect in custody, faces 6 federal charges
description: The suspect in the assassination and attempted assassination of two Minnesota lawmakers has been captured, Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz confirmed in a news conference. The suspect in the killing of a Minnesota lawmaker and her husband in addition to the shooting of another lawmaker and his wife also visited two more politicians’ homes, according to authorities. #CNN #News

title: A look back at when Donald Trump announced his presidential bid 10 years ago today
description: CNN's Inside Politics talks with to a panel of analysts who covered Trump's presidential bid on this day, 10 years ago. #CNN #News

title: Gallant says US has an obligation to help Israel's operation in Iran
description: Former Israeli Defense Minister Yoav Gallant has encouraged the United States to help more with Israel's Iran conflict, telling CNN's Bianna Golodryga that President Donald Trump “has the option to change the Middle East and influence the world.”  #CNN #News

title: What we know about key Iranian nuclear site
description: It’s key to Iran's nuclear program: the Fordow plant - in a mountain lair where hundreds of centrifuges, hidden possibly 90 meters underground, enrich uranium to 60%. CNN’s Nick Paton Walsh explains what we know about the key site in Israel’s crosshairs. #cnn #news #israel #iran

Thompson, the acting US attorney for the District of Minnesota, said at a news conference Monday.  #CNN #News

title: Trump slams G7 for kicking out Russia
description: President Donald Trump kicked off his visit to the G7 summit in Canada by criticizing nations for kicking out Russia eleven years ago. #CNN #News

Iran and Israel have traded unprecedented air and missile strikes, after Israel launched a sweeping air offensive on Iran on Friday claiming it’s in a bid to stop it from building an atomic weapon.

title: The biggest moments from Karen Read murder trial closing arguments
description:
The jury is deliberating the fate of Karen Read in the murder trial of her Boston Police Officer boyfriend, John O’Keefe. CNN’s Jean Casarez shares the biggest moments from closing arguments of the trial.

#cnn #news #karenreadcase #boston

title: CNN sees crater from Iranian strike

title: Storm chaser captures 'unprecedented' view of monster hailstones falling from sky
description:
Storm chaser and research scientist Sean Waugh has documented softball sized (or greater) hailstones in freefall with an ultra-high-tech camera mounted on a retrofitted research vehicle. The goal – to study and better understand what makes gigantic hail form, and how to better detect it and ultimately improve severe weather warnings. Sean speaks with CNN Meteorologist Derek Van Dam while on the road, capturing imagery of this very impactful and expensive natural phenomenon.

#cnn #news #weather #climate #hailstorm

title: CNN asks Israeli opposition leader what happens if US doesn't join Israel's fight against Iran
description: It would be in “everybody’s interest” for the US to join Israel in its fight against Iran, Israeli opposition leader Yair Lapid told CNN as tensions between the two nations continued to rise. Lapid who spoke to CNN’s Nic Robertson outside a Tel Aviv building struck by Iranian missiles, said he trusts President Trump will “do the right thing for America but also for the world.”  #CNN #News

title: Juror dismissed in Sean ‘Diddy’ Combs’ criminal trial
description: The judge in the Sean “Diddy” Combs trial has dismissed juror No. 6 over the juror’s inconsistent disclosures about where he lives and with whom. Juror No. 6 will be replaced by the first alternate juror. #cnn #news #diddy #diddytrial #juror

title: Flash flood destroys apartment building
description: An apartment building in West Virginia partially collapsed as flash floods hit the area. The governor's office said at least five people are dead and four people remain missing following the floods. #cnn #news #westvirginia

title: What Spaun was thinking before epic putt

title: ‘He’s going to face a tough room’: Enten on G7 countries’ opinion of Trump

title: New barrage of Iranian attacks hit Israel as conflict enters fourth day
description: The deadly conflict between Israel and Iran has entered its fourth day, with both sides widening their attacks. Overnight, Iran struck an Israeli oil refinery and damaged part of the power grid. In Israel, explosions were seen and residential buildings were hit.  #CNN #News

description: Residents in Tel Aviv, Israel, are reeling after another round of Iranian strikes on the city overnight. CNN’s International Diplomatic Editor Nic Robertson visits a street in the center of the city where buildings were severely damaged and windows blown out by Iranian missiles. #CNN #News

title: Suspect in Minnesota lawmaker shootings has been captured
description: Vance Boelter, the suspect in the shootings of two Minnesota lawmakers and their spouses, was arrested on Sunday. A local police chief described the chase to capture Boelter as the “largest manhunt in the state’s history.” #CNN #News

title: Suspected Minnesota shooter captured
description: Vance Boelter, the suspect in the assassination and attempted assassination of two Minnesota lawmakers, has been captured, Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz confirmed in a news conference late Sunday. #cnn #news #minnesota #boelter

title: Investigators provide update on search for suspect who killed Minnesota lawmaker and husband

title: Iran and Israel launch more missiles
description: Iran launched a new barrage of missiles at Israel Sunday evening, with an explosion seen in the coastal city of Haifa. Israel said it began another series of strikes on military targets across Iran.

title: CNN visits site of deadly Iranian missile strike
description: CNN’s Clarissa Ward reports from Tamra, a village in northern Israel inhabited by predominantly Palestinian citizens of Israel, where multiple civilians were killed after an Iranian rocket struck their home.

title: Scene outside assassinated state representative's home
description: CNN's Whitney Wild is outside the home of Minnesota State Representative Melissa Hortman, who was shot and killed in a "politically motivated assassination" along with her husband early Saturday morning. Police are still searching for the suspect. #cnn #cnnnews

title: Videos show aftermath of strikes on Israeli city of Haifa
description: A building was damaged in the northern Israeli city of Haifa, according to the Israeli search and rescue organization ZAKA, after the Israeli military detected more missile launches from Iran. Explosions were captured in the city, with smoke rising above the Haifa skyline.

title: What we know about the Minnesota shooting suspect
description: Vance Boelter, the 57-year-old suspect sought by authorities for allegedly shooting Democratic lawmakers in Minnesota on Saturday, worked for a security company that advertised a fleet of “police type vehicles,” and other equipment that could potentially have aided him in appearing to be a police officer during the shooting. #cnn #news #minnesota

title: Israel strikes Iran’s capital
description: Israeli strikes have hit the Iranian capital of Tehran on Sunday in yet another escalation of the ongoing conflict. Israel’s military had previously said it was targeting military and nuclear complexes in Iran, although there are no known such complexes in these areas of the capital. #cnn #news #israel #iran

title: Minnesota Senator: Rise in political threats ‘out of hand’
description: Sen. Amy Klobuchar spoke out against online threats aimed at lawmakers following the shooting deaths of State Rep. Melissa Hortman, the leading Democrat in the Minnesota House, and her husband. Gov. Tim Walz described the incident as a “politically motivated assassination” and said the same individual shot Democratic State Sen. John Hoffman and his wife, both of whom survived. #CNN #News

title: John Delony on what to tell #dad on Father’s Day
description: Dr. John Delony speaks to millions of listeners on his popular podcast about mental health, family and relationships. As a therapist, he’s used to offering advice to struggling fathers, but we asked him about the biggest lessons he’s learned as a dad. #cnn #news #fathersday #father #dad #advice #mentalhealth #lifeadvice #therapist

title: Shooting at Salt Lake City ‘No Kings’ march
description: Officers responded to gunshots at a “No Kings” march in Salt Lake City, Utah and took three people into custody in relation to the incident. One person was transferred to the hospital with life-threatening injuries. Salt Lake City police said the motive for the shooting was under investigation. #cnn #news #trump #nokings #nokingprotest #saltlakecity

title: In the rubble of a deadly Iranian missile attack

Israel’s national emergency service Magen David Adom (MDA) reported a “direct hit” on a residential building in the Palestinian-Israeli town of Tamra, killing at least three women and a 13-year-old girl. A later wave of strikes struck buildings in a residential area in the central Israeli city of Bat Yam, killing several people. #cnn #news #israel #iran

title: Iran and Israel trade strikes

title: Police chief gives details on #Minnesota shooting
description: The suspect in the assassination and attempted assassination of two Minnesota lawmakers has been identified as Vance Boelter, two law enforcement officials briefed on the case tell CNN. Law enforcement found a hit list in the Minnesota suspect’s car that contained nearly 70 names – including pro-abortion rights advocates and lawmakers in other states – a law enforcement official briefed on the matter told CNN. Brooklyn Park Police Chief Mark Bruley described what happened when officers first arrived at Senator Hoffman's home. #cnn #news #minnesota

Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said Israel coordinated with the United States “in advance” of the attack on Iran, and the Trump administration “knew about the strike.” The US military is helping to intercept Iranian missiles and drones, a US official told CNN.
 #CNN #News

title: Marines guard federal building in LA
